        "71026": {
          "vnum": 71026,
          "name": "Western Hall",
          "description": "Blocks of shattered stone lie strewn about this wide hallway, obscuring the green and yellow checkerboard tiles decorating the floor. Most of the stones were once part of the ceiling, but a few possess the delicately carved lines of sculpture. A fine green dust coats everything in sight. The hallways continues north, and a door opens to the south.",
