        "71027": {
          "vnum": 71027,
          "name": "Barren Courtyard",
          "description": "Shards of brightly colored tile scattered in the dusty soil suggest that this courtyard was once a place of great beauty. Smashed stone and streaks of charcoal black ash have replaced the earlier decor, offering few pleasantries for the eye. The buildings to the east remains standing, as does the wall of the building to the west, though the remaining stones may soon fall victim to the scythe of Time. The courtyard continues to the north, and to the south you spot an exit from the ruins.",
