        "71028": {
          "vnum": 71028,
          "name": "Eastern Hall",
          "description": "Pitted and cracked, the bare stones of this hallway reflect the ancient hatreds that led to their destruction. Except for a score of small piles of crushed feathers and bones, the hall is devoid of life and furnishings. The scent of death is strong here, rising from the piles and hanging in the still air. To the north, the hallway continues, and to the west lies a barren courtyard.",
