        "71029": {
          "vnum": 71029,
          "name": "Silent Chamber",
          "description": "The floors, walls, and ceiling of this small room are tiled with sections of bright yellow stone. In the center of the room, atop a raised platform, rises a statue of a miniature nehva tree. Carved perhaps from the same stone as the tiles, the statue is painted to appear fairly realistic. As you enter, you notice that the tiles, though not pliant, completely absorb the sound of your footsteps.",
